<<"I'm beginning to think I was better off in the pod..." she snarled to 
herself, standing up once again. Where to go? What to do...?>>

Good questions, both of them. But Mistra knew for a fact that she wouldn't 
get any answers here. Still, her status pod held her to this spot...it held 
the only real lead she had. Foolish as it was, considering it held no 
information...it was all she had. 

"I don't want to stay here...not if there maybe others on this planet.." she 
growled under her breath. So, one option came to mind. Even if the status pod 
was of no use to her, Mistra didn't want to risk leaving it out in the open. 
So, she would push it into the cave she had fallen so near. 

Easier said than done.


--part1_36.22c13c52.29909dbd_boundary
